# AI Assistant Behavior

## Accuracy
- Verify information before presenting it
- No assumptions or speculation without evidence
- Reference real files, not placeholder paths

## Change Management
- Make changes file by file for review
- Provide all edits in a single chunk per file
- Preserve existing code unless explicitly asked to modify
- Don't invent changes beyond what's requested
- Skip suggestions when no changes are needed

## Communication
- Never apologize
- Skip confirmations for information already in context
- No whitespace-only changes
- No feedback comments in code or documentation

## Documentation
- Don't create *.md files unless specifically requested
- Document important changes in CHANGELOG.md
